WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.200
Chapter number 12.

00:00:01.200 --> 00:00:03.680
And a couple of people have asked me recently,

00:00:03.680 --> 00:00:06.179
are we gonna get to the book of Revelation?

00:00:06.179 --> 00:00:09.300
And Lord willing, that will be next Sunday evening

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:11.699
that we'll return to the book of Revelation.

00:00:11.699 --> 00:00:16.540
And as we entered into 2026, had a few things on my heart

00:00:16.540 --> 00:00:18.059
that I wanted to be able to share with us

00:00:18.059 --> 00:00:21.819
as a church family with regard to some things on Wednesday,

00:00:21.819 --> 00:00:23.159
some things on Sunday.

00:00:23.159 --> 00:00:25.739
And so we've had some opportunity to be able to do that.

00:00:25.739 --> 00:00:29.620
And for two weeks here on Sunday evenings in 2026,

00:00:29.620 --> 00:00:32.479
and I've not preached all the Sunday evenings in 2026.

00:00:32.479 --> 00:00:34.659
Of course, we were snowed out one week

00:00:34.659 --> 00:00:37.240
and I was in traveling one week.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:39.000
And then we had brother Tim preached

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:40.020
one of the Sunday nights.

00:00:40.020 --> 00:00:41.900
We just had some things going on.

00:00:41.900 --> 00:00:46.000
And, but I've had the opportunity to preach two messages

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:49.959
that I entitled, Even So, Minister.

00:00:49.959 --> 00:00:51.799
And as we looked at those particular messages,

00:00:51.799 --> 00:00:54.119
we're looking at the truth of 1 Peter 4,

00:00:54.119 --> 00:00:55.159
verses 10 and 11,

00:00:55.159 --> 00:00:58.200
understanding that we've been given a spiritual gift

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:01.700
and the importance of understanding spiritual gifts,

00:01:01.700 --> 00:01:04.379
biblically, what the Bible speaks of

00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:06.059
with regard to spiritual gifts.

00:01:06.059 --> 00:01:09.180
And then having the understanding that,

00:01:09.180 --> 00:01:12.419
okay, God said that every man hath received the gift.

00:01:12.419 --> 00:01:15.339
And so therefore I have a spiritual gift.

00:01:15.339 --> 00:01:18.839
If I'm saved, I've been gifted, I've been equipped.

00:01:18.839 --> 00:01:21.500
And what is my spiritual gift

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:24.019
and how do I use my spiritual gift?

00:01:24.019 --> 00:01:28.019
And really that's been the thought for those two messages

00:01:28.839 --> 00:01:31.519
we've studied through a variety of passages of scripture.

00:01:31.519 --> 00:01:32.360
Now, this evening,

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:34.720
as we come to 1 Samuel chapter number 12,

00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:35.839
I'm gonna deal with this subject

00:01:35.839 --> 00:01:38.319
that I've simply titled from the passage of scripture,

00:01:38.319 --> 00:01:39.959
Serve the Lord.

00:01:39.959 --> 00:01:42.279
Now, the reality is that there's a lot of passages

00:01:42.279 --> 00:01:47.160
I could go to and preach a message entitled, Serve the Lord.

00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:50.319
And we find that there's a theme throughout the scriptures,

00:01:50.319 --> 00:01:51.540
not only in the Old Testament,

00:01:51.540 --> 00:01:52.720
but also in the New Testament,

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:54.800
that we are to serve the Lord.

00:01:54.800 --> 00:01:57.599
In fact, maybe you've heard somebody say it this way,

00:01:57.599 --> 00:02:01.059
that we've been saved to serve.

00:02:01.059 --> 00:02:04.019
You ever hear somebody say that, use that terminology?

00:02:04.019 --> 00:02:05.980
No doubt from Ephesians chapter number two,

00:02:05.980 --> 00:02:07.139
when you get to verse number 10,

00:02:07.139 --> 00:02:09.580
we are his workmanship, amen.

00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:12.100
And we're created unto good works.

00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:14.740
And we understand we don't do good works to get saved,

00:02:14.740 --> 00:02:17.179
we don't do good works to stay saved,

00:02:17.179 --> 00:02:20.100
but because we've been saved,

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:22.279
because of the work that he's done in our lives,

00:02:22.279 --> 00:02:24.199
then we become his servants.

00:02:24.220 --> 00:02:28.339
And what a joy it is to serve the Lord.

00:02:28.339 --> 00:02:30.380
As you come to 1 Samuel chapter number 12,

00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:32.740
I would say this, the life of Samuel is a life

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:34.860
that is just worth studying.

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:37.100
I mean, so many wonderful, valuable lessons

00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:40.339
that you can learn as you study through the life of Samuel.

00:02:40.339 --> 00:02:42.820
And a couple of years ago in Sunday school,

00:02:42.820 --> 00:02:45.220
we did a series through the life of Samuel

00:02:45.220 --> 00:02:46.539
and looked at a number of things

00:02:46.539 --> 00:02:49.020
that were just so important for us

00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:50.500
to learn from the scriptures.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:52.500
God has recorded it for us,

00:02:52.500 --> 00:02:56.000
not simply so that we would have the historical account,

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.520
but so that we could take truth and apply it in our lives

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:01.520
so that we could be challenged in our own walk with God.

00:03:01.520 --> 00:03:04.039
And so we come here to 1 Samuel chapter number 12,

00:03:04.039 --> 00:03:07.100
we understand that Samuel, if you were to look back,

00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:08.660
and we won't take time to do so,

00:03:08.660 --> 00:03:13.660
but Samuel is the direct result of fervent prayer, amen.

00:03:14.600 --> 00:03:17.039
Hannah prayed fervently, she prayed for a son,

00:03:17.039 --> 00:03:20.080
she prayed fervently, she prayed specifically,

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:22.440
and God answered her prayer.

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:24.500
And she made a promise and that promise

00:03:24.500 --> 00:03:28.300
was that she would give her son back to the Lord

00:03:28.300 --> 00:03:31.820
and she made good on the promise that she made to God.

00:03:31.820 --> 00:03:33.779
And here's something that I find in life

00:03:33.779 --> 00:03:36.500
and there are times in which people deal

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:39.220
with a particular situation, a circumstance,

00:03:39.220 --> 00:03:42.419
maybe it's a physical malady,

00:03:42.419 --> 00:03:44.419
some difficulty that they're facing,

00:03:44.419 --> 00:03:46.339
they'll say, God, if you just take this away,

00:03:46.339 --> 00:03:47.779
then I'll serve you with my life.

00:03:47.779 --> 00:03:48.619
You ever hear somebody make

00:03:48.619 --> 00:03:50.500
some kind of declaration like that?

00:03:50.520 --> 00:03:54.919
Oh, that's a dangerous thing, it's a dangerous thing.

00:03:54.919 --> 00:03:56.880
I know a lot of people that have made commitments,

00:03:56.880 --> 00:03:59.360
vows, if we could even use that word,

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:03.940
in that fashion and God worked and God delivered

00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:08.279
and God did and then they just went and did their own thing

00:04:08.279 --> 00:04:11.360
and that's a terrible, terrible situation.

00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:15.360
And we find that Hannah gave her son back to the Lord

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:18.119
as she promised to do so and you read through

00:04:18.140 --> 00:04:20.820
the book of 1 Samuel and you have wonderful opportunities

00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:24.059
to read of the life and ministry of Samuel.

00:04:24.059 --> 00:04:26.899
You don't read of his death until 1 Samuel 25,

00:04:26.899 --> 00:04:28.820
so there are a whole lot of things that happen

00:04:28.820 --> 00:04:33.140
in Samuel's life even after this portion of scripture

00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:35.420
that we'll look at in 1 Samuel chapter number 12,

00:04:35.420 --> 00:04:37.859
but really if we look at chapter number 12,

00:04:37.859 --> 00:04:40.619
we see some things as God would provide for us

00:04:40.619 --> 00:04:42.640
and I wanna get specifically to the subject

00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:45.739
of serving the Lord, but we find in the first several verses,

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.040
verses one through five, that Samuel begins

00:04:48.040 --> 00:04:49.959
to recall his own ministry.

00:04:49.959 --> 00:04:52.000
Notice what he says in verse one.

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.140
He says, and Samuel said unto all Israel,

00:04:54.140 --> 00:04:56.359
so he gathers the people, he begins to speak to them.

00:04:56.359 --> 00:04:58.679
By the way, this was something that happened

00:04:58.679 --> 00:04:59.799
on more than one occasion.

00:04:59.799 --> 00:05:02.220
He says, behold, I have hearkened unto your voice

00:05:02.220 --> 00:05:03.799
and all that you have said unto me

00:05:03.799 --> 00:05:05.519
and have made a king over you.

00:05:05.519 --> 00:05:08.279
God was their king, they had a theocracy

00:05:08.279 --> 00:05:11.220
and they wanted a king, they wanted a human king

00:05:11.220 --> 00:05:13.000
and the scriptures tell us they desired

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:15.019
to be like the other nations.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:16.839
Amen?

00:05:16.839 --> 00:05:19.720
And of course, Samuel disgrieved him.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:22.980
He was grieved in his heart at the request of the people

00:05:22.980 --> 00:05:25.140
and God said, no, they've not rejected you,

00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:27.700
they've rejected me and give them a king

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:30.100
and we know that the first king is Saul

00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:31.579
and he'd be anointed to be the king

00:05:31.579 --> 00:05:33.899
and we find that Samuel says, I've done.

00:05:33.899 --> 00:05:36.059
I have hearkened unto your voice, I've hearkened

00:05:36.059 --> 00:05:38.140
to their voice, but obviously the voice of God

00:05:38.140 --> 00:05:41.260
and verse two, and now behold, the king walketh before you

00:05:41.260 --> 00:05:43.940
and I am old and gray headed and behold,

00:05:43.940 --> 00:05:47.700
my sons are with you and I have walked before you

00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:52.260
from my childhood unto this day.

00:05:52.260 --> 00:05:54.959
You begin to think about Samuel kind of recalling

00:05:54.959 --> 00:05:57.899
his own ministry and even in making that statement

00:05:57.899 --> 00:05:59.820
in verse number two to end the verse

00:05:59.820 --> 00:06:03.179
that I have walked before you from my childhood

00:06:03.179 --> 00:06:06.820
unto this day, how that simple statement covers

00:06:06.820 --> 00:06:11.179
so many years and so many things that God used Samuel

00:06:11.179 --> 00:06:13.940
to accomplish in just a summary statement,

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:16.380
but we understand that Samuel was known

00:06:16.380 --> 00:06:17.859
as being a man of God.

00:06:18.739 --> 00:06:20.380
The man of God is in this city.

00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:22.820
You'll read that, man, what a powerful truth

00:06:22.820 --> 00:06:25.339
and the influence and impact that he had

00:06:25.339 --> 00:06:28.700
and then we find in verses six through 12

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:31.859
that Samuel would begin to rehearse the works of God.

00:06:31.859 --> 00:06:33.619
In fact, in verse six, notice it says,

00:06:33.619 --> 00:06:35.220
and Samuel said unto the people,

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:38.299
it is the Lord that advanced Moses and Aaron

00:06:38.299 --> 00:06:41.119
and that brought your fathers up out of the land

00:06:42.059 --> 00:06:43.880
of Egypt, I like that little phrase, it is the Lord.

00:06:43.880 --> 00:06:45.399
Listen, it wasn't Moses and Aaron,

00:06:45.399 --> 00:06:47.920
it wasn't their skill, their wisdom,

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:49.679
it was God that was working.

00:06:49.679 --> 00:06:52.359
In verse seven, now therefore stand still

00:06:52.359 --> 00:06:54.559
that I may reason with you before the Lord.

00:06:54.559 --> 00:06:57.739
Notice what the Bible says, of all the righteous acts

00:06:57.739 --> 00:07:01.799
of the Lord, which he did to you and to your fathers.

00:07:01.799 --> 00:07:04.200
Oh, the number of things that could be rehearsed

00:07:04.200 --> 00:07:07.220
as you begin to think about what God did for his people

00:07:07.220 --> 00:07:09.920
and how God worked on the behalf of his people

00:07:09.959 --> 00:07:11.760
and then as we go through the text

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:14.359
and again, I'm getting to the end of it here

00:07:14.359 --> 00:07:17.320
because in verses 13 through 25,

00:07:17.320 --> 00:07:21.119
we find that what Samuel does is he reminds the people

00:07:21.119 --> 00:07:22.720
to serve the Lord.

00:07:22.720 --> 00:07:25.839
Now, it's interesting for he said, as we read already

00:07:25.839 --> 00:07:28.980
in verse number two, that I am old and gray-headed.

00:07:28.980 --> 00:07:30.959
We understand that Samuel will not die

00:07:30.959 --> 00:07:34.160
for several more chapters in the book of 1 Samuel

00:07:34.160 --> 00:07:39.160
but no doubt, his place in scripture, if you will,

00:07:39.559 --> 00:07:43.440
begins to fade as you begin to see the dominance

00:07:43.440 --> 00:07:46.000
of Saul and David and so on and so forth

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:47.959
as you read through the book of 1 Samuel

00:07:47.959 --> 00:07:50.679
and yes, when David is fleeing from Saul,

00:07:50.679 --> 00:07:53.480
he goes to Samuel, he goes to the man of God

00:07:53.480 --> 00:07:55.440
and what a great decision that was

00:07:55.440 --> 00:07:58.679
but you begin to see how the lens of scripture,

00:07:58.679 --> 00:08:02.519
if you will, that had been so fixated on the life

00:08:02.519 --> 00:08:05.160
and ministry of Samuel begins to shift

00:08:05.160 --> 00:08:07.679
and Samuel says, I'm old and I'm gray-headed

00:08:07.679 --> 00:08:10.799
and he stands before Israel and he reminds them

00:08:10.799 --> 00:08:13.000
of the importance of serving the Lord.

00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:14.320
Now, why do I say all of that?

00:08:14.320 --> 00:08:16.279
Because I'm reminded of Joshua at the end

00:08:16.279 --> 00:08:19.200
of the book of Joshua when he was used of God.

00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:23.399
The Bible tells us that Joshua was Moses' minister.

00:08:23.399 --> 00:08:25.579
He was a man that knew how to serve God.

00:08:25.579 --> 00:08:27.739
He was a man that served the Lord faithfully.

00:08:27.739 --> 00:08:31.799
By the way, he was, I believe and I would argue

00:08:31.799 --> 00:08:36.039
that Joshua was chosen by God to be the next human leader

00:08:36.039 --> 00:08:38.880
of the nation of Israel because he was already serving.

00:08:40.119 --> 00:08:42.239
He was already doing, he was already serving,

00:08:42.239 --> 00:08:44.119
he was already engaged in the work.

00:08:44.119 --> 00:08:46.080
It wasn't that God went and found somebody

00:08:46.080 --> 00:08:48.739
that was just on the sideline somewhere doing nothing,

00:08:48.739 --> 00:08:50.520
having no part and said, yeah, I think

00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:51.760
they'll be the next leader.

00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:53.880
No, he was already serving.

00:08:53.880 --> 00:08:56.559
He was already engaged, he was already involved

00:08:56.559 --> 00:08:59.239
and we find that Joshua, after you go through

00:08:59.239 --> 00:09:03.020
the entire book of Joshua and the record that is given

00:09:03.020 --> 00:09:04.520
with the conquering of the land

00:09:04.520 --> 00:09:06.640
and the division of the land and you find

00:09:06.640 --> 00:09:08.520
that Joshua does something very similar.

00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:12.719
At the end of the book of Joshua, he calls the people.

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:15.599
He's gonna challenge them and we're familiar.

00:09:15.599 --> 00:09:17.479
In fact, Brianna mentioned at lunch

00:09:17.479 --> 00:09:20.479
that recently a chapel speaker there at Vision

00:09:20.479 --> 00:09:23.640
asked the question, how many of you at your homes

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:26.599
have a plaque or a sign that says,

00:09:26.599 --> 00:09:30.400
as for me and my house, we will serve the Lord.

00:09:30.400 --> 00:09:32.799
And I asked her, I said, is it almost everybody

00:09:32.799 --> 00:09:35.000
in the college student body that raised their hand?

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.359
And she said, yeah, I mean, maybe somebody didn't,

00:09:37.359 --> 00:09:39.700
but it sure seemed like everyone raised their hand.

00:09:39.700 --> 00:09:43.080
And many of us this evening, we may have a placard,

00:09:43.080 --> 00:09:46.239
a hanging, a painting of something in our home

00:09:46.239 --> 00:09:50.320
that says, as for me and my house, we will serve the Lord.

00:09:50.320 --> 00:09:52.700
And Joshua made that declaration,

00:09:52.700 --> 00:09:55.799
but understand that Joshua also challenged

00:09:55.799 --> 00:09:59.880
the people of Israel to serve the Lord.

00:09:59.880 --> 00:10:02.680
We come here to 1 Samuel chapter 12

00:10:02.680 --> 00:10:06.140
and we understand that Samuel now

00:10:06.140 --> 00:10:09.140
understanding the way in which things

00:10:09.140 --> 00:10:11.600
are transitioning and all that's taking place

00:10:11.600 --> 00:10:15.780
and this opportunity to have the nation before him

00:10:15.780 --> 00:10:18.600
and to address them and to challenge them.

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:21.200
He says in v. 14,

00:10:21.200 --> 00:10:23.640
"...if ye will fear the Lord..."

00:10:23.640 --> 00:10:25.360
Notice the first reference.

00:10:25.360 --> 00:10:27.200
"...and serve Him,

00:10:27.200 --> 00:10:28.480
and obey His voice,

00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:31.840
and not rebel against the commandment of the Lord,

00:10:31.840 --> 00:10:34.180
then shall both ye and also the king

00:10:34.180 --> 00:10:35.520
that reigneth over you

00:10:35.520 --> 00:10:39.140
continue following the Lord your God."

00:10:39.140 --> 00:10:40.820
Skip down to v. 20 if you will.

00:10:40.820 --> 00:10:42.820
The Bible says, "...and Samuel said unto the people,

00:10:42.820 --> 00:10:46.360
Fear not, you have done all this wickedness,

00:10:46.360 --> 00:10:48.740
yet turn not aside from following the Lord..."

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:49.780
Notice this.

00:10:49.780 --> 00:10:51.320
"...but serve the Lord..."

00:10:51.320 --> 00:10:53.280
Notice what it says.

00:10:53.280 --> 00:10:57.160
"...with all your heart."

00:10:57.180 --> 00:11:01.060
No half-hearted service.

00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:07.060
I mean, it's serve the Lord with all your heart.

00:11:07.060 --> 00:11:10.220
Aren't you thankful that Jesus gave it all?

00:11:10.220 --> 00:11:11.440
Amen?

00:11:11.440 --> 00:11:12.640
Often we sing the song,

00:11:12.640 --> 00:11:13.940
Jesus paid it all,

00:11:13.940 --> 00:11:15.060
and certainly He did.

00:11:15.060 --> 00:11:16.060
I'm thankful.

00:11:16.060 --> 00:11:18.700
Listen, He didn't just make a down payment.

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:20.400
You know what a down payment is?

00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:22.240
A down payment means you still got a responsibility

00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:24.040
to pay the rest of it.

00:11:24.040 --> 00:11:24.900
Amen?

00:11:24.900 --> 00:11:25.860
You ever go buy a car

00:11:25.900 --> 00:11:27.280
and they say, you're down payment,

00:11:27.280 --> 00:11:28.860
and then they say, here's the rest of your payments,

00:11:28.860 --> 00:11:30.120
we'll split them up by the month,

00:11:30.120 --> 00:11:31.780
and we'll do it for 180 months

00:11:31.780 --> 00:11:32.940
or whatever they say, right?

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:34.440
I mean, they just want to finance it longer

00:11:34.440 --> 00:11:35.820
and longer and longer and longer.

00:11:35.820 --> 00:11:36.440
Why?

00:11:36.440 --> 00:11:39.860
Because they make more and more and more money.

00:11:39.860 --> 00:11:40.960
No, no.

00:11:40.960 --> 00:11:42.920
He paid it all.

00:11:42.920 --> 00:11:44.040
And here Samuel says,

00:11:44.040 --> 00:11:47.920
"...serve the Lord with all your heart."

00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:49.880
V. 23, "...moreover, as for me,

00:11:49.880 --> 00:11:51.800
God forbid that I should sin against the Lord

00:11:51.800 --> 00:11:53.540
in ceasing to pray for you,

00:11:53.540 --> 00:11:55.800
but I will teach you the good

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:57.860
and the right way.

00:11:57.860 --> 00:12:00.040
Only fear the Lord

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:03.660
and serve Him in truth."

00:12:03.660 --> 00:12:04.500
Here you see it again,

00:12:04.500 --> 00:12:07.340
"...with all your heart."

00:12:07.340 --> 00:12:08.840
And then he says this,

